Direct css solution is available only in Firefox so far (Oct 2019) and it uses [:dir() CSS pseudo class](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:dir) this way:

    #sidebar.active:dir(ltr) { left: 0;}
    #sidebar.active:dir(rtl) { right: 0;}

Support table [here](https://caniuse.com/#feat=css-dir-pseudo).

For all other browsers, best way is to add a body class depending on text direction. So, once you have:

    &lt;body class=&quot;text-rtl&quot;&gt;

... than later on you can in one stylesheet place:

    #sidebar.active { left: 0;}
    .text-rtl #sidebar.active { right: 0;}

That&#39;s it.

